POA/HSEQ-POL/003 
DRUG & ALCOHOL POLICY 
This  statement  applies  to  all  employees  of PRIMAX  OUTDOOR  ADVERTISING and  those 
doing  business  with  us  while  on  our  premises  or  site  projects,  the  case  point  is  not  to 
intrude  into  private  lives  of  our  employees,  we  recognize that  involvement  with  alcohol  or 
other drugs off the job eventually takes its toll on job performance 
Our concern is to ensure that employees report to work in condition to perform their duties 
safely  and  efficiently  in  the  interest  of  their  fellow  workers  and  customers  as  well  as 
themselves. 
 PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING will not tolerate or condone substance abuse 
.It is our policy to maintain a workplace free from alcohol and other drug abuse 
and its effect 
 PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING shall terminate or take other displinary action 
to employees engaged in sale, use possession or transfer of illegal drugs or 
controlled substances 
 PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING shall committee resources necessary to achieve 
and maintain a drug free and alcohol free environment 
 Each PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING Employee has a responsibility to report to 
work at all times free of alcohol or other drugs and their effects  
 Employees shall be tested for the presence of alcohol where their actions, 
appearance, behaviors or conduct suggests alcohol may be impacting on their 
ability to work effectively and safely  
 Random Testing Employees shall be subject to be randomly selected for testing 
for the presence of alcohol 
 Support company efforts to eliminate alcohol and other drug abuse among 
employees where its exists 
All employees and other stakeholders are required to observe this policy to enable 
PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING to achieve its targets and objectives on health and 
safety standards 
 
 
 
