POA/HSEQ-POL/004 
 
PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT (PPE) POLICY 
 
We are committed to protecting our employee from occupational injuries and 
illness that could occur during our work operations through the appropriate use 
of PPE. 
PPE will not be used as the sole source of protection from injury to workers but 
will be used in conjunction with other controls to reduce the risk to as low as 
practically possible. 
 
It is our policy to: 
1. Accept and adopt industry- recognized standards concerning the use of PPE 
and also comply with the requirements of the law. 
2. Ensure that each employee is trained on the correct use of PPE and is also 
made aware of the safety procedures which are associated with the use of 
PPE. 
3. Provide each employee with appreciate PPE to protect them from job 
specific hazards identified after a job safety analysis has been done. 
4. Ensure that PPE is used correctly for the purpose for which it has been 
issued. 
5. To take disciplinary action against non-compliance with this policy and also 
recognize good observance of the requirements of the policy. 
 
 
 
 
