POA/HSEQ-POL/005 
QUALITY POLICY 
It is the policy of PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING to supply work and services of high and 
consistent quality to   its Clients. These will   be in   accordance with the Company's 
organizational goals, client’s requirements  and  expectations that include the needs of our 
clients. This policy will  be reviewed at regular intervals to  ensure that it is still  up to date 
and relevant. 
 
The PRIMAX  OUTDOOR  ADVERTISING Quality policy defines the management of  the 
organization responsible for quality, which through periodic management reviews, ensures 
the suitability, achievement and maintenance of the Company's quality objectives and that 
continuous improvement is affected. 
 
Quality Objectives; 
 To ensure that client needs and expectations are fulfilled with the aim of achieving 
client satisfaction. 
 To ensure timely completion of projects undertaken according to projects master 
programme. 
 To minimize wastage of materials (Banners, Rubber, steel, & etc) 
 To reduce  quality  problem  i.e.:  repair  works  &  remedial  work  to  as  low  cases  as 
possible. 
 To integrate “Quality, Environmental, Health & Safety” in all our processes and at 
all  levels  of  our  organization  and  ensure  that  they  are  integral  part  of  our 
management systems. 
 To  develop  close  relationship  with  the  stake  holders  and  industry  experts  to 
ensure that the completed projects are in tandem with their requirements. 
 
All   operations shall   be carried out as defined in the manuals   and safe operating 
procedures. Deviation from the procedures must be first  notified to the Managing 
Director. He is responsible for final  approval of all  changes to procedures prior to 
implementation. 
It is part of the Company's training program that this policy is understood, implemented 
and maintained at all levels in the organization. 
 
 
