POA/HSEQ-POL/006 
WASTE MANAGEMENT POLICY 
Purpose  
PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING accepts its environmental responsibilities and recognizes 
its obligations to contribute to the resolution of global and local environmental issues by 
minimizing its environmental impact. POA generates significant quantities of waste through 
its diverse operations. Accordingly, POA aims to avoid waste generation where possible, 
reduce waste production and reuse or recycle waste that is unavoidably produced to 
minimize waste disposed of to landfill.  
 This policy supports compliance with all relevant waste management legislation and 
requirements as detailed in our Environmental Legislation Register  
Policy Statements 
PRIMAX OUTDOOR ADVERTISING will strive to satisfy its legal and sustainability 
obligations by adopting the following principles:  
 Considering the waste generation implications of projects and procurement 
decisions at an early stage and consider lifecycle information in purchasing 
decisions and project management;  
 Controlling and efficiently using materials and resources to reduce waste 
generation;  
 Identifying and enabling the reuse of waste items wherever feasible, either 
internally or in association with third parties; considering onsite treatment 
options such as composting;  
 Recycling items and materials which cannot be reused, endeavoring to recycle 
these items in the highest specification materials possible;  
 Monitoring and measuring all waste, reuse and recycling streams generated by 
the Company, reporting on trends to staff, and senior management;  
 Setting agreed targets for reducing site waste generation and waste to landfill;  
 Utilizing Company based research and commercial resources and working with 
the Company waste management contractor to identify waste reduction, reuse 
or recycling project opportunities;  
 Complying with all relevant legal requirements and other guidance to which the 
Company subscribes;  
 Communicating with staff, and visitors to ensure all are aware of the Waste 
Management Strategy, and associated procedures/guidelines. 
 
 
